---
description: Use the project Conda environment
alwaysApply: true
---

When running shell commands for this project, always use the Conda environment named `cosyvoice`.

For Python commands, use:

    conda run -n cosyvoice python

For package installation, use:

    conda run -n cosyvoice pip install <package>

For running tests, use:

    conda run -n cosyvoice pytest

Do not use the system Python.

Do not use plain `python`, `python3`, `pip`, or `pip3` unless the Conda environment is already active.

Before running Python-related commands, prefer verifying the interpreter with:

    conda run -n cosyvoice python -c "import sys; print(sys.executable)"

If a command needs to run a Python module, use:

    conda run -n cosyvoice python -m <module>
